# Revyl (mobile dev loops + cloud devices)

Use this rule when the user asks to run, change, preview, debug, screenshot, or
verify a mobile app on a Revyl device.

Load `revyl-mcp-dev-loop` and prefer the Revyl MCP `dev` profile. It delegates
to the canonical CLI behavior while adding state, structured outcomes, and
inline images. Use shell CLI commands only when MCP is unavailable.

Share the viewer immediately, distinguish device readiness from build success,
verify through screenshots and semantic validation, and stop owned sessions
when finished. Load the cloud-agent skill only when that context applies.

Never expose credentials or launch-variable values.
